{"id":18091,"date":"2019-02-19T15:19:23","date_gmt":"2019-02-19T09:49:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=18091"},"modified":"2021-07-26T16:31:34","modified_gmt":"2021-07-26T11:01:34","slug":"g-d-bakshi","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/g-d-bakshi\/","title":{"rendered":"Major General G. D. Bakshi Wiki, Age, Army Career, Wife, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/G-D-Bakshi-photo.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18094\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/G-D-Bakshi-photo.jpg\" alt=\"G D Bakshi photo\" width=\"516\" height=\"383\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/G-D-Bakshi-photo.jpg 516w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/G-D-Bakshi-photo-300x223.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p><b>Gagandeep Bakshi or G. D. Bakshi\u00a0<\/b>is a retired Indian Army officer. He served in <strong>Jammu &amp; Kashmir Rifles<\/strong>. He has been awarded several medals for his distinguished service in the Indian Army.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce33258d0c\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce33258d0c\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/g-d-bakshi\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/g-d-bakshi\/#Family\" title=\"Family\">Family<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/g-d-bakshi\/#Military_Career\" title=\"Military Career\">Military Career<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/g-d-bakshi\/#Controversies\" title=\"Controversies\">Controversies<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/g-d-bakshi\/#AwardsHonours\" title=\"Awards\/Honours\">Awards\/Honours<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/g-d-bakshi\/#Facts\" title=\"Facts\">Facts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Wiki\/Biography<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Bakshi was born in 1950 (<strong>Age 70 years: as in 2020<\/strong>) in Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India. Since childhood, he had a wish to serve in the Indian Army. His brother, Captain Raman Bakshi, was the first martyr in the 1965 Indo-Pak war at the young age of 23. In the honour of his brother, one street of\u00a0Jabalpur has been named, &#8216;Raman Bakshi Marg.&#8217; He completed his basic education from\u00a0St. Aloysius Senior Secondary School in Jabalpur. For higher education, he joined National Defence Academy and Indian Military Academy from where he completed his graduation.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Family<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>The names of his family members are not known. The only information is about his brother, Raman Bakshi who died in the Indo-Pak war of 1965.<\/p>\n<div class=\"flex-video flex-video-youtube\"><iframe title=\"The 1965 Indo - Pakistan War - Preview | #EPICSpecials\" width=\"1060\" height=\"596\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/VDCePz6Kv40?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Military_Career\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Military Career<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>He was commissioned in the Indian Army in 1971 and played an important role in the 1971 Indo-Pak War. He also played a crucial role to counter the terror activities in Punjab in 1984. In the Kargil War of 1999, he commanded the Batallion and successfully led the operations against Pakistan.<a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/G-D-Bakshi.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-18147\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/G-D-Bakshi.jpg\" alt=\"G D Bakshi\" width=\"640\" height=\"358\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/G-D-Bakshi.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/G-D-Bakshi-300x168.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Apart from it, Bakshi commanded the Romeo Force to counter terrorist activities in the\u00a0Rajouri-Poonch districts of Jammu and Kashmir and succeeded in pacifying the region.\u00a0He has been the Directorate General of Military Operations twice and was the first BGS (IW) at HQ\u00a0Northern Command (India), where he dealt with Information Warfare and Psychological Operations.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Controversies\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Controversies<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2016, when he was delivering his speech over National Security in IIT Madras, a student named Abhinav Surya labelled his speech hate-mongering. Regarding this, Abhinav Surya sent a letter to the department on which he wrote, &#8220;I am still not able to digest the fact that the institute has given a platform to such a speech filled with hatred, instigating violence among students. A lecture that was heavily loaded with brewing enmity, inhumanity, and glorification of brutality.&#8221;<a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/GD-Bakshi.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-18146\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/GD-Bakshi.jpg\" alt=\"G.D. Bakshi\" width=\"528\" height=\"363\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/GD-Bakshi.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/GD-Bakshi-300x206.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 528px) 100vw, 528px\" \/><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Several times, he has poked fun at Mahatma Gandhi and other Freedom Fighters.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In July 2020, he used profane language on a live debate on a news channel. While appearing as one of the panelists on a live debate on Republic TV, he called a panelist madar****. Mr. Bakshi received heavy criticism for using such profane language. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_18091_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_18091_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_18091_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_18091_1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_18091_1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.freepressjournal.in\/india\/m-twitter-in-shock-as-major-gen-gd-bakshi-curses-on-a-live-show\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">The Free Press Journal<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"AwardsHonours\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Awards\/Honours<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Vishisht Seva Medal for commanding the battalion in the Kargil War<\/li>\n<li>Sena Medal for counter-terror operations in the rugged mountains of Kishtwar<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Facts\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Facts<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Bakshi is also a writer. He has penned many books on Military matters. He has written about 24 books and more than 100 papers in popular journals.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He has been a teacher at the Indian Military Academy, Dehradun.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Bakshi has also been a teacher at the prestigious Defence Services Staff College, Wellington, Tamil Nadu.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He has also taught at the National Defence College, Delhi for two years before being retired in 2008.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>His hobbies are; Reading, Working out, Yoga.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>His latest book, Bose: An Indian Samurai, was published in 2016.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_18153\" style=\"width: 334px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Bose-An-Indian-Samurai.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-18153\" class=\" wp-image-18153\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Bose-An-Indian-Samurai.jpg\" alt=\"Bose: An Indian Samurai, a book was written by G. D. Bakshi\" width=\"324\" height=\"477\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Bose-An-Indian-Samurai.jpg 435w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/Bose-An-Indian-Samurai-204x300.jpg 204w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 324px) 100vw, 324px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-18153\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Bose: An Indian Samurai, a book written by G. D. Bakshi<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div><div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_label_expand_18091_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_18091_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_18091_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_18091_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">References<\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_plus_18091_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_18091_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_18091_1.toggleClass(cl